"v.弄碎；崩毁 【英】 v. 弄碎 (to break into crumbs or small pieces)；崩毁(to fall to pieces; disintegrate) 【考】 friable : crumble / malleable : alter(易碎的容易破碎/可 改变的容易改变)反义词：friable(易 碎的)-not easily crumbled(不易破碎的) 【例】 crumble the bread / a crumbling church. v. 弄碎(把...弄成小块); 崩毁 = disintegrate = collapse 【类】friable: crumble = malleable: alter 易碎的容易破碎 = 可改变的容易改变 【反】friable(adj 易碎的; 脆的)－not easily crumbled(不易破碎的) 【记】cram 塞，塞的时候会弄碎里面的东西；crush压碎 + 音：崩； 【相关】grumble 嘟囔怨言，隆隆响，同rumble, rumble (车开过)隆隆声,低沉地说 crumble (v.)  late 15c., kremelen, from Old English *crymelan, presumed frequentative of gecrymman ""to break into crumbs,"" from cruma (see crumb). The -b- is 16c., probably on analogy of French-derived words like humble, where it belongs, or by influence of crumb. Related: Crumbled; crumbling."
